<p class="">Seeing that it has been decided to establish now the skeleton of a Ministry, can the Prime Minister say that all its activities in peace-time will be confined purely to foreign information, and that there will be no attempt in times of peace to interfere with the work of the Press or the legitimate activities of this country; and are we to understand that, whatever its duties and responsibilities may be in time of war, at the present time its activities are to be definitely limited to those of foreign propaganda and information?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
